      • isInventoryAccessible

        public boolean isInventoryAccessible(UUID uuid,
                            Block block)
        Check if the player with the given UUID has access rights for the given block.

        Note that not all protection plugins may support checking by UUID yet; if a plugin which doesn't support UUID checking is in force, then this method will return false if the player is offline, even if they would normally have permission.

        Parameters:
        uuid - UUID to check (may be null; if so, always return true)
        block - block to check
        Returns:
        true if the player may access the block's contents

      • playerCanBuild

        public boolean playerCanBuild(UUID uuid,
                     Block block,
                     BlockProtection.Operation op)
        Check if the given player UUID has construction rights for the given block.

        Note that not all protection plugins may support checking by UUID yet; if a plugin which doesn't support UUID checking is in force, then this method will return false if the player is offline, even if they would normally have permission.
        Parameters:
        uuid - the player's uuid
        block - the block to check for
        Returns:
        true if the player has construction rights; false otherwise
